  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NONE

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_DEFAULTHIDE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_DEFAULTHIDE Default as a hidden/disabled column.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_DEFAULTSORT
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_DEFAULTSORT Default as a sorting column.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_WIDTHSTRETCH
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_WIDTHSTRETCH Column will stretch. Preferable with horizontal scrolling disabled (default if table sizing policy is _SizingStretchSame or _SizingStretchProp).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_WIDTHFIXED
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_WIDTHFIXED Column will not stretch. Preferable with horizontal scrolling enabled (default if table sizing policy is _SizingFixedFit and table is resizable).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NORESIZE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NORESIZE Disable manual resizing.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOREORDER
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOREORDER Disable manual reordering this column, this will also prevent other columns from crossing over this column.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOHIDE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOHIDE Disable ability to hide/disable this column.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOCLIP
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOCLIP Disable clipping for this column (all NoClip columns will render in a same draw command).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOSORT
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOSORT Disable ability to sort on this field (even if ImGuiTableFlags_Sortable is set on the table).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOSORTASCENDING
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOSORTASCENDING Disable ability to sort in the ascending direction.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOSORTDESCENDING
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOSORTDESCENDING Disable ability to sort in the descending direction.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_NOHEADERWIDTH
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_NOHEADERWIDTH Disable header text width contribution to automatic column width.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_PREFERSORTASCENDING
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_PREFERSORTASCENDING Make the initial sort direction Ascending when first sorting on this column (default).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_PREFERSORTDESCENDING
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_PREFERSORTDESCENDING Make the initial sort direction Descending when first sorting on this column.

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_INDENTENABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_INDENTENABLE Use current Indent value when entering cell (default for column 0).

  - name: TABLECOLUMN_INDENTDISABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLECOLUMN_INDENTDISABLE Ignore current Indent value when entering cell (default for columns > 0). Indentation changes _within_ the cell will still be honored.

  - name: TABLE_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NONE

  - name: TABLE_RESIZABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_RESIZABLE Enable resizing columns.

  - name: TABLE_REORDERABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_REORDERABLE Enable reordering columns in header row (need calling TableSetupColumn() + TableHeadersRow() to display headers)

  - name: TABLE_HIDEABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_HIDEABLE Enable hiding/disabling columns in context menu.

  - name: TABLE_SORTABLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SORTABLE Enable sorting. Call TableGetSortSpecs() to obtain sort specs. Also see ImGuiTableFlags_SortMulti and ImGuiTableFlags_SortTristate.

  - name: TABLE_NOSAVEDSETTINGS
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOSAVEDSETTINGS Disable persisting columns order, width and sort settings in the .ini file.

  - name: TABLE_CONTEXTMENUINBODY
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_CONTEXTMENUINBODY Right-click on columns body/contents will display table context menu. By default it is available in TableHeadersRow().

  - name: TABLE_ROWBG
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_ROWBG Set each RowBg color with ImGuiCol_TableRowBg or ImGuiCol_TableRowBgAlt (equivalent of calling TableSetBgColor with ImGuiTableBgFlags_RowBg0 on each row manually)

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSINNERH
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSINNERH Draw horizontal borders between rows.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSOUTERH
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSOUTERH Draw horizontal borders at the top and bottom.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSINNERV
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSINNERV Draw vertical borders between columns.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSOUTERV
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSOUTERV Draw vertical borders on the left and right sides.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSH
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSH Draw horizontal borders.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSV
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSV Draw vertical borders.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSINNER
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSINNER Draw inner borders.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERSOUTER
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERSOUTER Draw outer borders.

  - name: TABLE_BORDERS
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_BORDERS Draw all borders.

  - name: TABLE_NOBORDERSINBODY
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOBORDERSINBODY [ALPHA] Disable vertical borders in columns Body (borders will always appears in Headers). -> May move to style

  - name: TABLE_NOBORDERSINBODYUNTILRESIZE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOBORDERSINBODYUNTILRESIZE [ALPHA] Disable vertical borders in columns Body until hovered for resize (borders will always appears in Headers). -> May move to style

  - name: TABLE_SIZINGFIXEDFIT
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SIZINGFIXEDFIT Columns default to _WidthFixed or _WidthAuto (if resizable or not resizable), matching contents width.

  - name: TABLE_SIZINGFIXEDSAME
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SIZINGFIXEDSAME Columns default to _WidthFixed or _WidthAuto (if resizable or not resizable), matching the maximum contents width of all columns. Implicitly enable ImGuiTableFlags_NoKeepColumnsVisible.

  - name: TABLE_SIZINGSTRETCHPROP
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SIZINGSTRETCHPROP Columns default to _WidthStretch with default weights proportional to each columns contents widths.

  - name: TABLE_SIZINGSTRETCHSAME
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SIZINGSTRETCHSAME Columns default to _WidthStretch with default weights all equal, unless overriden by TableSetupColumn().

  - name: TABLE_NOHOSTEXTENDX
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOHOSTEXTENDX Make outer width auto-fit to columns, overriding outer_size.x value. Only available when ScrollX/ScrollY are disabled and Stretch columns are not used.

  - name: TABLE_NOHOSTEXTENDY
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOHOSTEXTENDY Make outer height stop exactly at outer_size.y (prevent auto-extending table past the limit). Only available when ScrollX/ScrollY are disabled. Data below the limit will be clipped and not visible.

  - name: TABLE_NOKEEPCOLUMNSVISIBLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOKEEPCOLUMNSVISIBLE Disable keeping column always minimally visible when ScrollX is off and table gets too small. Not recommended if columns are resizable.

  - name: TABLE_PRECISEWIDTHS
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_PRECISEWIDTHS Disable distributing remainder width to stretched columns (width allocation on a 100-wide table with 3 columns: Without this flag: 33,33,34. With this flag: 33,33,33). With larger number of columns, resizing will appear to be less smooth.

  - name: TABLE_NOCLIP
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOCLIP Disable clipping rectangle for every individual columns (reduce draw command count, items will be able to overflow into other columns). Generally incompatible with TableSetupScrollFreeze().

  - name: TABLE_PADOUTERX
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_PADOUTERX Default if BordersOuterV is on. Enable outer-most padding. Generally desirable if you have headers.

  - name: TABLE_NOPADOUTERX
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOPADOUTERX Default if BordersOuterV is off. Disable outer-most padding.

  - name: TABLE_NOPADINNERX
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_NOPADINNERX Disable inner padding between columns (double inner padding if BordersOuterV is on, single inner padding if BordersOuterV is off).

  - name: TABLE_SCROLLX
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SCROLLX Enable horizontal scrolling. Require 'outer_size' parameter of BeginTable() to specify the container size. Changes default sizing policy. Because this create a child window, ScrollY is currently generally recommended when using ScrollX.

  - name: TABLE_SCROLLY
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SCROLLY Enable vertical scrolling. Require 'outer_size' parameter of BeginTable() to specify the container size.

  - name: TABLE_SORTMULTI
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SORTMULTI Hold shift when clicking headers to sort on multiple column. TableGetSortSpecs() may return specs where (SpecsCount > 1).

  - name: TABLE_SORTTRISTATE
    type: number
    desc: |
      TABLE_SORTTRISTATE Allow no sorting, disable default sorting. TableGetSortSpecs() may return specs where (SpecsCount == 0).

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NONE

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOTITLEBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOTITLEBAR Disable title-bar

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NORESIZE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NORESIZE Disable user resizing with the lower-right grip

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOMOVE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOMOVE Disable user moving the window

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOSCROLLBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOSCROLLBAR Disable scrollbars (window can still scroll with mouse or programmatically)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOSCROLLWITHMOUSE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOSCROLLWITHMOUSE Disable user vertically scrolling with mouse wheel. On child window, mouse wheel will be forwarded to the parent unless NoScrollbar is also set.

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOCOLLAPSE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOCOLLAPSE Disable user collapsing window by double-clicking on it

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSAUTORESIZE
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSAUTORESIZE Resize every window to its content every frame

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOBACKGROUND
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOBACKGROUND Disable drawing background color (WindowBg, etc.) and outside border. Similar as using SetNextWindowBgAlpha(0.0f).

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOSAVEDSETTINGS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOSAVEDSETTINGS Never load/save settings in .ini file

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOMOUSEINPUTS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOMOUSEINPUTS Disable catching mouse, hovering test with pass through.

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_MENUBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_MENUBAR Has a menu-bar

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_HORIZONTALSCROLLBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_HORIZONTALSCROLLBAR prior to calling Begin() to specify width. Read code in imgui_demo in the "Horizontal Scrolling" section.

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOFOCUSONAPPEARING
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOFOCUSONAPPEARING Disable taking focus when transitioning from hidden to visible state

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOBRINGTOFRONTONFOCUS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOBRINGTOFRONTONFOCUS Disable bringing window to front when taking focus (e.g. clicking on it or programmatically giving it focus)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSVERTICALSCROLLBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSVERTICALSCROLLBAR Always show vertical scrollbar (even if ContentSize.y < Size.y)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSHORIZONTALSCROLLBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSHORIZONTALSCROLLBAR Always show horizontal scrollbar (even if ContentSize.x < Size.x)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSUSEWINDOWPADDING
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_ALWAYSUSEWINDOWPADDING Ensure child windows without border uses style.WindowPadding (ignored by default for non-bordered child windows, because more convenient)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NONAVINPUTS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NONAVINPUTS No gamepad/keyboard navigation within the window

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NONAVFOCUS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NONAVFOCUS No focusing toward this window with gamepad/keyboard navigation (e.g. skipped by CTRL+TAB)

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_UNSAVEDDOCUMENT
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_UNSAVEDDOCUMENT Append '*' to title without affecting the ID, as a convenience to avoid using the ### operator. When used in a tab/docking context, tab is selected on closure and closure is deferred by one frame to allow code to cancel the closure (with a confirmation popup, etc.) without flicker.

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NONAV
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NONAV ImGuiWindowFlags_NoNavInputs | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoNavFocus,

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NODECORATION
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NODECORATION ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse,

  - name: WINDOWFLAGS_NOINPUTS
    type: number
    desc: |
      WINDOWFLAGS_NOINPUTS ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMouseInputs | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoNavInputs | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoNavFocus,

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_NONE

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONLEFT
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONLEFT // For BeginPopupContext*(): open on Left Mouse release. Guaranteed to always be == 0 (same as ImGuiMouseButton_Left)

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONRIGHT
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONRIGHT // For BeginPopupContext*(): open on Right Mouse release. Guaranteed to always be == 1 (same as ImGuiMouseButton_Right)

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONMIDDLE
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONMIDDLE // For BeginPopupContext*(): open on Middle Mouse release. Guaranteed to always be == 2 (same as ImGuiMouseButton_Middle)

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONMASK
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONMASK

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONDEFAULT
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_MOUSEBUTTONDEFAULT

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_NOOPENOVEREXISTINGPOPUP
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_NOOPENOVEREXISTINGPOPUP For OpenPopup*(), BeginPopupContext*(): don't open if there's already a popup at the same level of the popup stack

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_NOOPENOVERITEMS
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_NOOPENOVERITEMS For BeginPopupContextWindow(): don't return true when hovering items, only when hovering empty space

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUPID
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUPID For IsPopupOpen(): ignore the ImGuiID parameter and test for any popup.

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUPLEVEL
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUPLEVEL For IsPopupOpen(): search/test at any level of the popup stack (default test in the current level)

  - name: POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUP
    type: number
    desc: |
      POPUPFLAGS_ANYPOPUP

  - name: DROPFLAGS_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_NONE

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCENOPREVIEWTOOLTIP
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCENOPREVIEWTOOLTIP By default, a successful call to BeginDragDropSource opens a tooltip so you can display a preview or description of the source contents. This flag disable this behavior.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCENODISABLEHOVER
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCENODISABLEHOVER By default, when dragging we clear data so that IsItemHovered() will return false, to avoid subsequent user code submitting tooltips. This flag disable this behavior so you can still call IsItemHovered() on the source item.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCENOHOLDTOOPENOTHERS
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCENOHOLDTOOPENOTHERS Disable the behavior that allows to open tree nodes and collapsing header by holding over them while dragging a source item.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCEALLOWNULLID
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCEALLOWNULLID Allow items such as Text(), Image() that have no unique identifier to be used as drag source, by manufacturing a temporary identifier based on their window-relative position. This is extremely unusual within the dear imgui ecosystem and so we made it explicit.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCEEXTERN
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCEEXTERN External source (from outside of dear imgui), won't attempt to read current item/window info. Will always return true. Only one Extern source can be active simultaneously.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_SOURCEAUTOEXPIREPAYLOAD
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_SOURCEAUTOEXPIREPAYLOAD Automatically expire the payload if the source cease to be submitted (otherwise payloads are persisting while being dragged)

  - name: DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTBEFOREDELIVERY
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTBEFOREDELIVERY AcceptDragDropPayload() will returns true even before the mouse button is released. You can then call IsDelivery() to test if the payload needs to be delivered.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTNODRAWDEFAULTRECT
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTNODRAWDEFAULTRECT Do not draw the default highlight rectangle when hovering over target.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTNOPREVIEWTOOLTIP
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTNOPREVIEWTOOLTIP Request hiding the BeginDragDropSource tooltip from the BeginDragDropTarget site.

  - name: DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTPEEKONLY
    type: number
    desc: |
      DROPFLAGS_ACCEPTPEEKONLY For peeking ahead and inspecting the payload before delivery.

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_NONE

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CHARSDECIMAL
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CHARSDECIMAL

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CHARSHEXADECIMAL
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CHARSHEXADECIMAL

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CHARSUPPERCASE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CHARSUPPERCASE Turn a..z into A..Z

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CHARSNOBLANK
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CHARSNOBLANK Filter out spaces, tabs

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_AUTOSELECTALL
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_AUTOSELECTALL Select entire text when first taking mouse focus

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_ENTERRETURNSTRUE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_ENTERRETURNSTRUE Return 'true' when Enter is pressed (as opposed to every time the value was modified). Consider looking at the IsItemDeactivatedAfterEdit() function.

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKCOMPLETION
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKCOMPLETION Callback on pressing TAB (for completion handling)

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKHISTORY
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKHISTORY Callback on pressing Up/Down arrows (for history handling)

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKALWAYS
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKALWAYS Callback on each iteration. User code may query cursor position, modify text buffer.

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKCHARFILTER
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKCHARFILTER Callback on character inputs to replace or discard them. Modify 'EventChar' to replace or discard, or return 1 in callback to discard.

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_ALLOWTABINPUT
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_ALLOWTABINPUT Pressing TAB input a '\t' character into the text field

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CTRLENTERFORNEWLINE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CTRLENTERFORNEWLINE In multi-line mode, unfocus with Enter, add new line with Ctrl+Enter (default is opposite: unfocus with Ctrl+Enter, add line with Enter).

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_NOHORIZONTALSCROLL
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_NOHORIZONTALSCROLL Disable following the cursor horizontally

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_ALWAYSOVERWRITE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_ALWAYSOVERWRITE Insert mode

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_READONLY
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_READONLY Read-only mode

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_PASSWORD
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_PASSWORD Password mode, display all characters as '*'

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_NOUNDOREDO
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_NOUNDOREDO Disable undo/redo. Note that input text owns the text data while active, if you want to provide your own undo/redo stack you need e.g. to call ClearActiveID().

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CHARSSCIENTIFIC
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CHARSSCIENTIFIC Allow 0123456789.+-*/eE (Scientific notation input)

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKRESIZE
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKRESIZE Callback on buffer capacity changes request (beyond 'buf_size' parameter value), allowing the string to grow. Notify when the string wants to be resized (for string types which hold a cache of their Size). You will be provided a new BufSize in the callback and NEED to honor it. (see misc/cpp/imgui_stdlib.h for an example of using this)

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKEDIT
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_CALLBACKEDIT Callback on any edit (note that InputText() already returns true on edit, the callback is useful mainly to manipulate the underlying buffer while focus is active)

  - name: INPUTFLAGS_ESCAPECLEARSALL
    type: number
    desc: |
      INPUTFLAGS_ESCAPECLEARSALL Callback on any edit (note that InputText() already returns true on edit, the callback is useful mainly to manipulate the underlying buffer while focus is active)

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NONE

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOALPHA
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOALPHA // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: ignore Alpha component (will only read 3 components from the input pointer).

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOPICKER
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOPICKER // ColorEdit: disable picker when clicking on color square.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOOPTIONS
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOOPTIONS // ColorEdit: disable toggling options menu when right-clicking on inputs/small preview.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOSMALLPREVIEW
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOSMALLPREVIEW // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: disable color square preview next to the inputs. (e.g. to show only the inputs)

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOINPUTS
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOINPUTS // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: disable inputs sliders/text widgets (e.g. to show only the small preview color square).

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOTOOLTIP
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOTOOLTIP // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: disable tooltip when hovering the preview.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOLABEL
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOLABEL // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: disable display of inline text label (the label is still forwarded to the tooltip and picker).

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOSIDEPREVIEW
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOSIDEPREVIEW // ColorPicker: disable bigger color preview on right side of the picker, use small color square preview instead.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NODRAGDROP
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NODRAGDROP // ColorEdit: disable drag and drop target. ColorButton: disable drag and drop source.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_NOBORDER
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_NOBORDER // ColorButton: disable border (which is enforced by default)

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHABAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHABAR // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: show vertical alpha bar/gradient in picker.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHAPREVIEW
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHAPREVIEW // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: display preview as a transparent color over a checkerboard, instead of opaque.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHAPREVIEWHALF
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_ALPHAPREVIEWHALF // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: display half opaque / half checkerboard, instead of opaque.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_HDR
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_HDR // (WIP) ColorEdit: Currently only disable 0.0f..1.0f limits in RGBA edition (note: you probably want to use ImGuiColorEditFlags_Float flag as well).

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYRGB
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYRGB [Display]    // ColorEdit: override _display_ type among RGB/HSV/Hex. ColorPicker: select any combination using one or more of RGB/HSV/Hex.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYHSV
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYHSV [Display]    // "

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYHEX
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_DISPLAYHEX [Display]    // "

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_UINT8
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_UINT8 [DataType]   // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: _display_ values formatted as 0..255.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_FLOAT
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_FLOAT [DataType]   // ColorEdit, ColorPicker, ColorButton: _display_ values formatted as 0.0f..1.0f floats instead of 0..255 integers. No round-trip of value via integers.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_PICKERHUEBAR
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_PICKERHUEBAR [Picker]     // ColorPicker: bar for Hue, rectangle for Sat/Value.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_PICKERHUEWHEEL
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_PICKERHUEWHEEL [Picker]     // ColorPicker: wheel for Hue, triangle for Sat/Value.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_INPUTRGB
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_INPUTRGB [Input]      // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: input and output data in RGB format.

  - name: COLOREDITFLAGS_INPUTHSV
    type: number
    desc: |
      COLOREDITFLAGS_INPUTHSV [Input]      // ColorEdit, ColorPicker: input and output data in HSV format.

  - name: COND_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      COND_NONE No condition (always set the variable), same as _Always

  - name: COND_ALWAYS
    type: number
    desc: |
      COND_ALWAYS No condition (always set the variable)

  - name: COND_ONCE
    type: number
    desc: |
      COND_ONCE Set the variable once per runtime session (only the first call will succeed)

  - name: COND_FIRSTUSEEVER
    type: number
    desc: |
      COND_FIRSTUSEEVER Set the variable if the object/window has no persistently saved data (no entry in .ini file)

  - name: COND_APPEARING
    type: number
    desc: |
      COND_APPEARING Set the variable if the object/window is appearing after being hidden/inactive (or the first time)

  - name: DIR_NONE
    type: number
    desc: |
      DIR_NONE

  - name: DIR_LEFT
    type: number
    desc: |
      DIR_LEFT

  - name: DIR_RIGHT
    type: number
    desc: |
      DIR_RIGHT

  - name: DIR_UP
    type: number
    desc: |
      DIR_UP

  - name: DIR_DOWN
    type: number
    desc: |
      DIR_DOWN

  - name: GLYPH_RANGES_DEFAULT
    type: number
    desc: |
      GLYPH_RANGES_DEFAULT // Basic Latin, Extended Latin

  - name: GLYPH_RANGES_GREEK
    type: number
    desc: |
      GLYPH_RANGES_GREEK // Default + Greek and Coptic

  - name: GLYPH_RANGES_KOREAN
    type: number
    desc: |
      GLYPH_RANGES_KOREAN // Default + Korean characters

  - name: GLYPH_RANGES_JAPANESE
    type: number
    desc: |
      GLYPH_RANGES_JAPANESE // Default + Hiragana, Katakana, Half-Width, Selection of 2999 Ideographs

  - name: GLYPH_RANGES_CHINESEFULL
    type: number
    desc: |
      GLYPH_RANGES_CHINESEFULL // Default + Half-Width + Japanese Hiragana/Katakana + full set of about 21000 CJK Unified Ideographs

